parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to lurch forward
or the pedal to go to the floor; extended stopping distance; poor braking ability; grinding noise from the brakes; intermittent release of brakes; and the ABS light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pads and rotors can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: and the need for frequent brake pad replacements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle continues to accelerate when the brake pedal is pressed to deactivate the cruise control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the upper ball joint can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also result in damage to the vehicle and other components.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
there is a squeaking noise from the front suspension
the wheel falls off while driving
and the ball joint breaks unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start after sitting for a couple of hours
and the vehicle requires a jump start to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper system can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents, especially during rain or snow.
symptoms: causing poor visibility for the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear window latch motor can cause the window to become stuck, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The rear window latch motor cycles but fails to release the window
causing the window to become stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electric Outside Review Mirror Switch Shorting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shorting of the electric outside review mirror switch can cause a noxious burning smell, create a fire hazard, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The electric outside review mirror switch shorts out
creating a burning smell and a hot switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating, rust buildup, and coolant leakage can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: rust buildup in radiator and coolant reservoir
